<span id="freeTextContainer7314985367591199712">Having read a previous book by this author and really enjoyed it I already had expectations of what I might expect to read but you know what? It surpassed them.<br/><br/>The first thing I would mention due to the 4 stars not 5 is because I preferred the previous book&apos;s storyline.<br/><br/>However, this author is brilliant at building suspense and keeping it moving throughout the novel. This is 400 pages and as I braced myself thinking the brilliant and intriguing start could not be maintained I was glad she proved </span>
  <span id="freeText7314985367591199712" style="display:none">Having read a previous book by this author and really enjoyed it I already had expectations of what I might expect to read but you know what? It surpassed them.<br /><br />The first thing I would mention due to the 4 stars not 5 is because I preferred the previous book's storyline.<br /><br />However, this author is brilliant at building suspense and keeping it moving throughout the novel. This is 400 pages and as I braced myself thinking the brilliant and intriguing start could not be maintained I was glad she proved me wrong as the suspense built up and the character's were so believable the book [unlike others I've read] actually got better and not worse as in some cases it can.<br /><br />The information was kept back and only fed through little by little to tease you into reading more and more because you need to know just why the main character is not allowed back in Texas and why would she risk going back?<br /><br />A fantastic book that lightly in some places, and direct in others mentions God and it is so refreshing to read a book like this that does not make you cringe. <br /><br />Will definitely read more from this author. <br /><br />I receive this in exchange for an honest review. x<br /></span>
